This is a small mappack that includes two aim/gungame maps. Aim_cirkular_dev and Aim_cirkular_aztek |Story| Aim_cirkular_dev is the original map. I build it one day six months ago in an attempt to learn a friend how to build maps with curved brush work. I never thought about releasing this map when i build it so I didn´t spend much time at details. When I was done with my teaching I thought that it was wasted work if I trashed it. So I spend additional ten min´ and added some ladders and spawnpoints. I called some friends and we played some gungame on it, it was realy fun. They liked the map and wanted me to upload it on banana. But I though that it wasn´t worth it. Now six months later, they still want me to upload it. I said : Ok i do it , but I think I want to change the texture theme first. So I loaded it up in hammer and changed all textures so i got a aztek/stone look at the whole thing. I also added some paths on the ground and some mild fog to make it harder to spot people on the other side of the map. And aim_cirkular_aztek was born. It´s cool what a couple of new textures can do to a map. That is also why I uploaded both versions, so you got the ability to compare them with each other. ok blabla...blabl.. |end of the Story| |General map features| (same on both maps) Spawnpoints: 16 Buyzone: yes, at spawn Sun: yes Nav-file: yes in the rar.file |final notes| |This two maps are most fun to play on a gg servers // Tip | Have fun and keep playing! /Alex If I choose to spend more time at this map, it would probably be a second "theme" change. So if you have any texture/theme suggestions feel free to post

===|| A Skill Map Pack - Tyr & Radi ||=== Date: September, 2008 Version: 1.0 Author: Daan Rijpkema & Moritz v/d Lugt Web: http://www.fpsbanana.com/studios/586 ======== Description: ======== All my current skill maps combined. It is set within small arenas with objects placed tactically forcing you to use skill to eliminate your enemies. The close quarters offer intense gunfights. These are texture maps. All maps are made for a maximum of 12 players. Most of these are indoors but there are also two outdoor maps (a little bit bigger) in respective day and night. All maps have buyzones and a nav file. I will also release all maps individually soon. If you (dis)like the maps or have suggestions/improvements please comment. These maps are probably also suitable for gungame and/or deathmatch maps. ======== Objective: ======== Use the objects and environment to beat your enemies in gunfights. Pure skill will save you from getting that one headshot you didn't deserve... ======== Instructions: ======== 1. Unzip the contents your cstrike folder folder (e.g. C:\Program Files\Valve\Steam\accountname\counter strike source\cstrike\).

**AIM_KARGO** BY UNREAL Designed for competitive gaming, the map is result of a strong desire to create an interactive environment for the player, where players are not only making a difference. Offering a reasonable level of detail, cranes carry bulky items that can make a difference during a round, they will cross between the player and his target adding an extra factor to the game. That is what the map focuses on, and its something that I love to do. Created for the mappingbase.de mapping contest sponsored by BFHosting.com and ESL.eu. _Sorry! The screenshots don't show some of the detail, due to being overlays and they don't appear because I was using a CFG._ This is the second time I do this kind of map, the first one being [awp_station](http://www.gamebanana.com/maps/152741 "awp_station").
**Map features:**
- Lightning - Interectative environment - Custom radar - Wallbangs possible - Custom textures - 64 Spawnpoints - Custom precipitation particles - ESL / BFHosting / MappingBase adverts (required for the contest) - Many others!
I couldn't decide whether to leave it as an AIM map or AWP map, so I made two versions for people who don't prefer one to other as well. I wanna thank everyone who suported me on this project and mappingbase for hosting this contest. If you plan on running this map on a Deathmatch server, please consider having the AWP version rather then the AIM version as its cleaner (no droped weapons). Feel free to download, comment & rate the map.
